OL,4,Cpatient
OL,6,F"The error was identified through our
OL,7,Fincident reporting process, and we
OL,8,Fhave worked closely with the Ms
OL,9,FCarrick-Smith's solicitors to ensure
OL,10,Fthe matter was resolved fairly.
OL,12,F"As a learning organisation, we are
OL,13,Fcommitted to reflecting on incidents
OL,14,Flike this to drive improvement and
OL,15,Fensure lessons are learned. Since this
OL,16,Fincident, we have implemented
OL,17,Fadditional measures and safeguards to
OL,18,Fminimise the risk of a similar error
OL,19,Foccurring in the future. We remain
OL,20,Fdedicated to continuously improving
OL,21,Fthe care and services we provide."
